 as the partys  candidate for the united states senate in california he is the author of multiple books and a play and is critical of current american drug laws gray has been a member of the california judicial council as well as the california judicial councils advisory committee on juvenile law the alcohol advisory board to the orange county board of supervisors the advisory board of the california department of alcohol and drug programs and the orange county law library he has also been a member of the board of councilors of the usc law school gray also introduced orange county to the peer court system where juvenile defendants travel to a school outside their district to have their actual cases tried by other teenagers in  gray was nominated by libertarian party convention delegates as the running mate of former new mexico governor gary johnson contents  background  judicial career   us senate candidacy  antiwar on drugs activism   vicepresidential candidacy  personal  works  essays  books  musical  references  external links backgroundedit born in washington dc and raised in the los angeles california area gray earned his undergraduate degree from the university of california los angeles in  after which he taught in the peace corps in costa rica gray returned to california and earned a law degree from the university of southern california law school in  judicial careeredit from  through  gray practiced law with the judge advocate generals corps of the us navy in guam and california after five years in private practice he was named to the santa ana municipal court in  by governor george deukmejian who then appointed gray to the orange county superior court in  gray retired as a judge in january  much of his legal career has dealt with drugrelated issues  us senate candidacyedit main article united states senate election in california  following an unsuccessful bid in  for the republican nomination for the congressional seat in californias th congressional district gray left the republican party and joined the libertarian party in  he openly contemplated becoming a candidate for the  libertarian presidential nomination but later decided to run for the us senate instead in november  he declared his candidacy for the us senate seat occupied by barbara boxer in california gray was a keynote speaker at the  libertarian national convention in march  gray defeated former libertarian party of california chair gail lightfoot in a statewide primary for the partys nomination for us senate gray suspended his judicial activities while running for the senate against incumbent democratic senator barbara boxer and republican bill jones gray received  votes  of the total vote finishing behind boxer jones and peace and freedom party candidate marsha feinland antiwar on drugs activismedit gray is an outspoken critic of drug laws and the war on drugs particularly in the state of california he was a proponent of the regulate control and tax cannabis act of  a statewide referendum measure that was defeated in the  california state elections he is the author of why our drug laws have failed and what we can do about it – a judicial indictment of the war on drugs  and is one of the  people featured in the  documentary american drug war the last white hope in early  gray was one of the four cosponsors of an initiative called regulate marijuana like wine had it passed the initiative would have regulated cannabis consumption and production like wine in california followed by national media the measure failed to collect the minimum number of signatures needed for qualification to be placed on the ballot in the  statewide election but garnered significant speculation about grays future in the libertarian party and in national politics  vicepresidential candidacyedit see also gary johnson presidential campaign  on april   the question what would you think of judge gray running for vice president was posted from grays facebook page and received numerous positive responses within three days of the posting media sources confirmed that gray had been chosen by  libertarian presidential candidate gary johnson to be his running mate should johnson receive the partys nomination at the  libertarian national convention gray then confirmed his candidacy for the libertarian vicepresidential nomination in an open letter to the partys convention delegates on may   gray won the libertarian party lp vicepresidential nomination on the first ballot with  of the vote he ran on the ticket with johnson who received the lp presidential nomination personaledit gray resides in newport beach california he is married and is the father of children william jennifer and ky worksedit essaysedit the functional libertarian series la times and life  liberty blog networks  booksedit why our drug laws have failed a judicial indictment of war on drugs temple university press  isbn   wearing the robe the art and responsibilities of judging in todays courts square one publishers  isbn   a voters handbook effective solutions to americas problems the forum press  isbn   musicaledit americans all abridged a musical in one act book music and lyrics by judge james p gray referencesedit  judicial experience of judge jim gray  judgejimgraycom retrieved  may   interview lp veep nominee jim gray bearing drift audio interview september   accessed september    a b c ca lp ‘exceptional lineup of speakers planned for ca libertarian convention ′ independent political report february   retrieved may     a b c d about – judge james p gray wwwjudgejimgraycom retrieved may     a b press release libertarian party congratulates judge jim gray on retirement lp org january   retrieved may     poll track  house races californias th district national journalcom  archived from the original on september   retrieved may     breidenbach michelle may   calif judge makes a plea for drug reform the post standard via highbeam research subscription required retrieved may     orange c