state electionshe is the author of why our drug laws have failed and what we can do about it – a judicial indictment of the war on drugs  and is one of the  people featured in the  documentary american drug war the last white hopein early  gray was one of the four cosponsors of an initiative called regulate marijuana like wine had it passed the initiative would have regulated cannabis consumption and production like wine in california followed by national media the measure failed to collect the minimum number of signatures needed for qualification to be placed on the ballot in the  statewide election but garnered significant speculation about grays future in the libertarian party and in national politicson april   the question what would you think of judge gray running for vice president was posted from grays facebook page and received numerous positive responses within three days of the posting media sources confirmed that gray had been chosen by  libertarian presidential candidate gary johnson to be his running mate should johnson receive the partys nomination at the  libertarian national convention gray then confirmed his candidacy for the libertarian vicepresidential nomination in an open letter to the partys convention delegates on may   gray won the libertarian party lp vicepresidential httpenwikipediaorgwikijamesp category education license standard youtube license show more show less loading autoplay when autoplay is enabled a suggested video will automatically play next up next this is why americans are losing their rights  duration  killingtime  views  richard dawkins exploding at bullshit in the bible  duration  truth seeker  views  ethan nadelmann why we need to end the war on drugs  duration  ted  views  worlds scariest drug documentary exclusive  duration  vice  views  the  economics  of police state militarism and war on drugs thomas e woods jr  duration  samuel ezerzer  views  warren buffetts top  rules for success warrenbuffett  duration  evan carmi